(354, 1, '2015-06-09 16:25:20', '2015-06-09 16:25:20', '<span style="color: #ff6600;"><strong>Scrum Master Training Overview</strong></span>\n\n- The Certified Scrum Master course takes a practical approach to understanding how Scrum works and how managers and team members will participate using Scrum.\n\n- During this class, participants will learn the Scrum and Agile principles and practices through enjoyable exercises, case studies, and round table discussion.\n\n-The goal of this training is to allow students to understand what to expect from Scrum and Agile, demystify the ideas and begin using these ideas in their day to day practices\n\n<span style="color: #ff6600;"><strong>Scrum Master Training Includes</strong></span>\n\n- Hard and soft copy of training materials.\n- 2 year membership to the Scrum Alliance.\n- Online knowledge assessment by Scrum Alliance for certification.\n\n<span style="color: #ff6600;"><strong>Scrum Master Training Agenda</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Day 1</strong>\nIntroductions\nExpectations\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Silent Sort exercise</p>\nThe Ball Points Game\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Process improvement game</p>\nLean, Agile, and Scrum\nScrum Process\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Sprint types exercise</p>\nScrum Master Role\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Working with the team\nChange agent in an organization\nLeadership and organizational aspects of\nimplementing Scrum</p>\nProduct Owner Role\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Working with stakeholders\nResponsibilities and expectations\nIdeal Product Owner exercise</p>\n<strong>Day 2</strong>\nRetrospectives\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Timeline retrospective exercise</p>\nThe Team\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">The Knot: a self organization simulation\nTeam attributes, model of formation\nCommon issues for Scrummasters</p>\nProduct Backlog, User Stories and Agile requirements\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">User story writing exercise</p>\nAgile Estimating and Planning\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Agile estimating\nStorypoints exercise\nPlanning Poker exercise</p>\nWhat is “Done?”\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Definition of done exercise</p>\n<strong>Next Certified Scrum Master Training</strong>\nLocation: Avenue Code, 400 Montgomery St. Ste 305\nSan Francisco, CA 94104\n\nCourse Price: $1,295\nCourse Date: March 9th and 10th (Mon - Tues), 2015\n\nTraining Time: 9:00am - 5:30pm\n\n<strong>Instructor: Robin Dymond</strong>\n\nRobin Dymond, CST is an international trainer and consultant in Scrum, Agile, and Lean methods. Robin Dymond offers Scrum Alliance certified Scrummaster and Product Owner training, and has trained over 3000 people in Canada, USA and Europe. A frequent speaker and author in the Agile community, Robin Dymond presented keynote talks and sessions at conferences including Agile Eastern Europe 2009, 2010, 2012, Agile 2006, 2008, 2010 and others. He produced the Main Stage at Agile 2009. From 2005-2007 Dymond consulted on the largest enterprise adoption of Scrum in a financial services company. He is managing partner of Innovel LLC, a Virginia based Lean Agile training and consulting company. Dymond started using Scrum and XP in 2002. Dymond has 24 years experience in software and a degree in Electrical Engineering from the University of Calgary, Canada.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nFor more questions, please contact info@avenuecode.com', '2-DAY CERTIFIED SCRUM MASTER TRAINING (Mar)', 'Certified Scrum Masters help project teams properly use Scrum, increasing the likelihood of the project&#039;s overall success.\nFrom this course, you will get:\n\n- Hard and soft copy of training materials.\n- 2 year membership to the Scrum Alliance.\n- Online knowledge assessment by Scrum Alliance for certification.\n\nNext available training will be on March 9th-10th (Mon - Tues), 2014', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '347-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-06-09 16:25:20', '2015-06-09 16:25:20', '', 347, 'http://localhost/acnew/347-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(355, 1, '2015-06-09 17:11:31', '2015-06-09 17:11:31', '', '2 Day Chef Fundamentals', '<p>Chef Fundamentals is a two day comprehensive instructor-taught training covering the basic architecture of Chef and its associated tools. This course aims to prepare key development, engineering, and operations staff to use Chef to write infrastructure. From this course, you will get:</p>\n<p>- Hands on exercises to reinforce the material</p>\n<p>- Code repository that can be used and modified to real business problems</p>\n<p style="color: #666666;">Next training will be on March 16-17th (Mon-Tues), 2015</p>', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '349-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-06-09 17:11:31', '2015-06-09 17:11:31', '', 349, 'http://localhost/acnew/349-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
